()IdentityEvent kya hai?
--🔹 1️⃣ IdentityEvent kya hai?
IdentityEvent = Ye ek object hai jo Identity (user/account) ke upar hone wale changes / events ko track karta hai.
Basically audit aur workflow purposes ke liye use hota hai.
Simple analogy:-
IdentityEvent = “Ravi ke account me kya change hua, kab aur kisne kiya” ka record.

🔹 2️⃣ IdentityEvent ka kaam:-
()Change Tracking:-
Identity me hone wale changes ko track karta hai,jaise:-
--Role assignment
--Entitlement add/remove
--Attribute update
()Audit:-
Compliance ke liye event ka record rakhta hai
()Trigger Workflows:-
Events ke basis pe workflows ya notifications start kar sakte hain.

🔹 3️⃣ IdentityEvent ke andar kya hota hai?
Field/Attribute	         Description
id	Unique:-------------ID of the event
identity:---------------Identity object jiske liye event hai
eventType:--------------Type of event (RoleAssigned / EntitlementRemoved / AttributeUpdated)
eventDate:--------------Kab event occur hua
initiator:--------------Kisne event trigger kiya (Admin / System)
target:-----------------Event ka target (Role / Entitlement / Account / Attribute)
status:-----------------Event ka current status (Pending / Completed / Failed)
comments:---------------Optional comments ya reason
workflowTriggered:------Kya event ne workflow trigger kiya (true/false)

🔹 6️⃣ Possible Statuses:-
Status	                Meaning
Pending:----Event generate hua, abhi process ho raha hai.
Completed:--Event successfully process ho gaya.
Failed:-----Event process me error aaya.

🔹 7️⃣ DB me store hota hai?
✅ Haan bhai, IdentityEvent DB table me store hota hai, aur har event ka audit trail maintain karta hai.
Ye table link hota hai Identity table ke saath (identityId)
EventType, Target, Initiator, EventDate, Status = columns
