🔹 1️⃣ Basic ID & Identity Methods:-
1️⃣ getId():-
Purpose: Event ka unique ID return karta hai
System.out.println(event.getId()); // EVT_1001

2️⃣ setId(String id):-
Purpose: Event ka ID assign karta hai
event.setId("EVT_1001");

3️⃣ hasId():-
Purpose: Check karta hai ID set hai ya nahi
System.out.println(event.hasId()); // true / false

4️⃣ getIdentity():-
Purpose: Event ke liye related Identity object return karta hai
Identity user = event.getIdentity();
System.out.println(user.getName()); // "Ravi Kumar"

5️⃣ setIdentity(Identity identity):-
Purpose: Event me Identity assign karta hai
event.setIdentity(raviIdentity);

6️⃣ hasIdentity():-
Purpose: Identity set hai ya nahi check karta hai
System.out.println(event.hasIdentity()); // true / false

🔹 2️⃣ Event Info Methods:-
7️⃣ getEventType():-
Purpose: Event ka type return karta hai (RoleAssigned, EntitlementRemoved, AttributeUpdated)
System.out.println(event.getEventType()); // "RoleAssigned"

8️⃣ setEventType(String type):-
Purpose: Event type assign karta hai
event.setEventType("RoleAssigned");

9️⃣ hasEventType():-
Purpose: EventType set hai ya nahi
System.out.println(event.hasEventType()); // true / false

10️⃣ getEventDate():-
Purpose: Event kab hua return karta hai
System.out.println(event.getEventDate()); // Fri Mar 27 10:00:00 IST 2026

11️⃣ setEventDate(Date date):-
Purpose: Event date assign karta hai
event.setEventDate(new Date());

12️⃣ hasEventDate():-
Purpose: EventDate set hai ya nahi check karta hai
System.out.println(event.hasEventDate()); // true / false

🔹 3️⃣ Initiator Methods:-
13️⃣ getInitiator():-
Purpose: Kisne event trigger kiya (Admin / System)
System.out.println(event.getInitiator()); // "Admin Amit"

14️⃣ setInitiator(String user):-
Purpose: Initiator assign karta hai
event.setInitiator("Admin Amit");

15️⃣ hasInitiator():-
Purpose: Initiator set hai ya nahi
System.out.println(event.hasInitiator()); // true / false

🔹 4️⃣ Target Methods:-
16️⃣ getTarget():-
Purpose: Event ka target return karta hai (Role / Entitlement / Account / Attribute)
System.out.println(event.getTarget()); // "SAP Role"

17️⃣ setTarget(Object target):-
Purpose: Event target assign karta hai
event.setTarget(sapRoleObject);

18️⃣ hasTarget():-
Purpose: Target set hai ya nahi
System.out.println(event.hasTarget()); // true / false

🔹 5️⃣ Status Methods:-
19️⃣ getStatus():-
Purpose: Event ka status return karta hai (Pending / Completed / Failed)
System.out.println(event.getStatus()); // "Completed"

20️⃣ setStatus(String status):-
Purpose: Status assign karta hai
event.setStatus("Completed");

21️⃣ hasStatus();-
Purpose: Status set hai ya nahi
System.out.println(event.hasStatus()); // true / false

🔹 6️⃣ Comments & Workflow Methods:-
22️⃣ getComments():-
Purpose: Event me comments return karta hai
System.out.println(event.getComments()); // "Quarterly role update"

23️⃣ setComments(String comments):-
Purpose: Event me comments set karta hai
event.setComments("Quarterly role update");

24️⃣ hasComments():-
Purpose: Comments exist karte hain ya nahi check karta hai
System.out.println(event.hasComments()); // true / false

25️⃣ isWorkflowTriggered():-
Purpose: Kya event ne workflow trigger kiya
System.out.println(event.isWorkflowTriggered()); // true / false

26️⃣ setWorkflowTriggered(boolean triggered):-
Purpose: Workflow trigger flag set karta hai
event.setWorkflowTriggered(true);

🔹 7️⃣ Utility Methods:-
27️⃣ toString():-
Purpose: Event ka readable string return karta hai
System.out.println(event.toString());
// IdentityEvent[id=EVT_1001, identity=Ravi Kumar, eventType=RoleAssigned, target=SAP Role, status=Completed]

28️⃣ equals(Object obj):-
Purpose: Compare karta hai do events ko

29️⃣ hashCode():-
Purpose: Unique hash code return karta hai, collections / DB ke liye.
